pageContext.claim: “In just one operation alone, our ICE officers arrested 355 MS-13 gang members on Long Island and in the New York City area. Of those, nearly half were present in the country because they took advantage of the Democrat-backed loophole granting entry to unaccompanied alien minors.”
pageContext.analysis: There was no operation that arrested 355 MS-13 gang members on Long Island. Since September 2016, according to Suffolk County police commissioner Geraldine Hart, there have been 335 arrests of 235 MS-13 gang members. There has not been an MS-13 murder in Suffolk county since April of 2017. The meaning of the second part of Trump's statement is unclear.
